is clearly related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dendy" authorityYear="1892" box="[400,516,880,906]" class="Calcarea" family="Lelapiidae" genus="Grantiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="40" pageNumber="243" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[400,516,880,906]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="243">Grantiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with which it shares the nail-form triactines, with reduced paired actines, that are bundled in long tracts. It has a thick wall and a leuconoid organization. The choanoskeleton is supported by giant diactines and
</td>
